name: Louis Armstrong Poster
description:
size: 24"×36″

This is a signed and numbered Louis Armstrong Poster out of a set of 500. Poster dimensions are 24 inches by 36 inches and are delivered in a shipping tube.

Louis Daniel Armstrong, also known as Satchmo and Pops, is one of the most recognized jazz artists of our time. He was an amazing trumpet player that originated out of New Orleans. Much of his prominence came from the instant recognition of his gravelly voice along with his ability to shift jazz from a collective performance to a solo performance. He also had great dexterity at being an improviser and great ability to blend melody and lyrics.

name: Darryl "D.M.C." McDaniels
description:
size: 24"×48″
Autographed by: Rev Run

This Audio art canvas of  Darryl "D.M.C." McDaniels is complete with speakers so that you can bump jam like “It’s Tricky” or “My Adidas”. This paining is done entirely on vinyl record. You can se the whole and broken records throughout the painting. If you look in the top right corner you can see the speaker. The Speaker in swired to a head phone jack that comes out the side of the painting for easy access. This painting is covered by plexi glass for protection.
